{
  "stem": "26765.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I went to the University of Illinois, Cook County School of Nursing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I received a diploma in nursing in 1957.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then I married.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And then while I have the children, I took courses, maybe one course at a time, and it took me about 10 years to get my bachelor's of science in nursing.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And then another five years I got my master's of science in nursing.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I've worked 24 years for the Chicago Public Schools as a nurse.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My son's name is Gerard Moeller.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My daughter's name is Kareen Moeller.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, they didn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, people at that time thought that it was better to let the subject rest, not to bring it up.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But what was especially difficult for me while I lived with my aunt and uncle-- and this was the big bone of contention with me.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My aunt was a German Jew by birth, but when she married my uncle, she converted to Catholicism.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And like many converts, they are extremely Catholic or Jewish, to whatever religion they convert.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But not only that, my aunt was enamored with everything German, everything German.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "She didn't make a distinction between the Nazis and the Germans.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I almost had a feeling that she did not want to hear about what had happened in Germany.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Only positive things were mentioned about Germany, and they went to Germany every year.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they moved back to Germany for a while, but she was not able to establish contact again, so she came back here because my brother and I were here.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
